query: What has been John Higgins' performance trend in the minor-ranking finals from 2010 to 2013?
summary: John Higgins' perform trend in minor-ranking finals from 2010 to 2013 is both consistent and successful with total six appearances in finals. He achieved three titles in these events and finished runner-up in other three. In 2010, he become winner of Ruhr Championship and runner-up in Prague Classic. In 2011, he faced defeat as runner-up in Players Tour Championship, Event 5. But he managed to bounce back with victories in 2012 Kay Suzanne Memorial Trophy and 2013 Bulgarian Open, and loss as runner-up in 2012 Bulgarian Open.
